<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"> <channel><title>Ian Barnes</title><description>Random thoughts</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link><atom:link href="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en</language> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:46:34 -0000</pubDate> <lastBuildDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:46:34 -0000</lastBuildDate> <ttl>1440</ttl> <generator>MkDocs RSS plugin - v1.17.3</generator> <image> <url>null</url> <title>Ian Barnes</title><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link> </image> <item> <title>Home</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Home&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Occasional random writing, sometimes with images. A mix of scientific /mathematical curiosities, “creative&#34; pieces, opinions. Might even becontrove...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/</guid> </item> <item> <title>About</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;About me&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Mugshot&#34; src=&#34;assets/2024-01-19-blue-check-shirt.jpg&#34;&gt;{ width=25% }&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I grew up in Sydney, studied pure mathematics and computer science at theAustra...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/about/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Visualisation of periodic surfaces</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Visualisation of periodic surfaces&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here are some images I generated many years ago while I was writing my [PhDthesis][thesis]. These surfaces are all the solutions of simple equationsinvolving trig functions, but are close to and share symmetry and topology withperiodic minimal surfaces, which are difficult to calculate and work with.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2020/12/20/visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Foucault&#39;s pendulum</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Foucault&#39;s pendulum&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;I visited the Panthéon yesterday, and saw the original Foucault&#39;s pendulum.Well, sort of. It&#39;s the same location, but it got taken down when the Panthéonbecame a church again for a while, and was then restored, and then the wirebroke and they had to replace it. And at some point the original 28kg bob wasreplaced with one almost twice as heavy. So it&#39;s a bit like the story about theaxe that&#39;s had three new handles and two new heads...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2022/08/07/foucaults-pendulum/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Another periodic surface image</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Another periodic surface image&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a follow-up to &lt;a href=&#34;2020-12-20-visualisation-of-periodic-surfaces.md&#34;&gt;Visualisation of periodicsurfaces&lt;/a&gt;. A while ago I sawthis 3D printed Gyroid model advertised online and couldn&#39;t resist it. Design by&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bathsheba.com/&#34;&gt;Bathsheba Grossman&lt;/a&gt;, printed on demand by&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.shapeways.com/product/QNFAKNW9Z/gyroid&#34;&gt;Shapeways&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2024/04/07/another-periodic-surface-image/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Oystercatchers</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Oystercatchers&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A sort of poem, with illustrations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/03/29/oystercatchers/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Cloud</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Cloud&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lying on my back&lt;br&gt;Stretching my glutes&lt;br&gt;Looking out the upside-down window&lt;br&gt;Leaves, wind, smears on the glass...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Jun 2025 14:45:54 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/feed_rss_updated.xml">Ian Barnes</source><comments>https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/null</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.ianbarnes.me.uk/2025/05/26/cloud/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Spiritual bypassing</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Spiritual bypassing&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The only way out is through.&lt;/em&gt;